sift (0.4-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New release
    - Added new primitive "to", for matching message recipient.
    - Added new primitive "body", for matching message bodies.
    - Allows "to" "from" and "subject" matching to be inverted.
      (For example "!from:foo@bar.com" - means messages not from foo@bar.com)
    - Use full regexps for matching messsage sender, recipient, or
      subjects.
    - Added caching, and dry-run command line arguments

 -- Steve Kemp <steve@steve.org.uk>  Wed, 30 Jul 2008 10:52:52 +0000

sift (0.3-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New release
    - Added better error handling.
    - Allow login details to come from the command line.
    - More consistent argument handling.
    - Removed all output unless running under --verbose

 -- Steve Kemp <steve@steve.org.uk>  Sat, 26 Apr 2008 10:22:01 +0000

